RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 34. Maiden Claiming Purse 8000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUE EVEN SCORE bumped with BRIANA HARPER at the start, was rated off the rail on the backstretch, roused two wide on the bend, fanned out further for he stretch run, rallied under urging and swept past TINA'S TAPIZAR the last twenty yards. TINA'S TAPIZAR soon shared the early lead from inside, moved clear when asked upper stretch, began to wear down inside the final furlong, was outfinished but easily second best. BRIANA HARPER a step slow at the start, was caught in crowding just out of the gate, bumped with BLUE EVEN SCORE, was hustled along between rivals, advanced from inside on the turn then could only move clear for third late. DART ATTACK broke in stride, was soon engaged by TINA'S TAPIZAR from inside then began to give way in the lane. FERGIE ATTACK fractious in the gate, soon trailed, stayed well off the inside and showed little.

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Even Score
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated off rail, roused 2 wide turn, 3 wide rally, got up late

ENTRY.NAME: Briana Harper
ENTRY.OWNER: Scates, Joseph A. and Hugh D.
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled between, saved ground turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Tina's Tapizar
ENTRY.OWNER: The Estate of Kenneth H Hutchens
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside, urged clear stretch, wore down late

ENTRY.NAME: Fergie Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious gate, showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Dart Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide speed, gave way between stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In A llowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WARM BEAUTY was away slowly, void of speed though hustled after the break, picked up her pace along the rail on the bend, angled out widest upper stretch, was all out and quickly overtook HALLIE'S RAINBOW nearing the wire. HALLIE'S RAINBOW set a pressured pace between horses on the backstretch, moved clear along the rail, was roused leaving the turn, lengthened command but did not have enough left in the waning yards. VIVA VIOLENCE prominent between horses, advanced three wide on the bend then leveled off the last furlong. SENORITA AURORA well placed from inside, began to flatten out before finishing a half mile. AMARI S. pressed from outside, did not keep up two wide on the bend and also flattened out for the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Senorita Aurora
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Viva Violence
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly between, 3 wide turn, evenly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Warm Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, inside turn, angled 4 wide stretch, got up

ENTRY.NAME: Hallie's Rainbow
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed between, inside turn, widened stretch, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Amari S.
ENTRY.OWNER: Lynch Harry E and Couch Ron
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, 2-3 path turn, flattened out stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ZARMAE broke outward, bumping GEORGE'S VISION, was kept close just off the inside, split horses two wide at the halfway point, quickly moved clear under urging, was just off the inside entering the lane, floated out some inside the last eighth, was challenged nearing the sixteenth marker, dug in, leaned on GEORGE'S VISION through the waning yards and prevailed. GEORGE'S VISION was taken outside early on, angled in entering the second turn, altered outside ZARMAE upper stretch, engaged the latter nearing the final sixteenth, lugged in some in the late going, leaning on ZARMAE, did not have enough nearing the wire but proved easily second best. ARGYBARGY BUCK shared the early lead from outside, did not stay with ZARMAE after a half mile, came into the stretch from path four and flattened out. OKLAHOMA HEAT failed to menace in a ground-saving trip. COPPER CROSSING was sent to dispute the pace from inside, also did not stay with ZARMAE after a half mile, came off the rail some on the second bend, altered in for a better path upper stretch but had little to offer.

ENTRY.NAME: Copper Crossing
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent inside, 2-3 path 2nd turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Zarmae
ENTRY.COMMENT: split foes 1/2, urged clear, 2-path into stretch, challenged,held

ENTRY.NAME: George's Vision
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in 2nd turn, angled 3 wide stretch, dueled late, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Argybargy Buck
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside speed, 3-4 path, flattened out last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: Oklahoma Heat
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 24000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WAIVER CLAIMING OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,500 FOR HORSES WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FEVER NATION hesitated at the break but moved clear of the rest after the first sixteenth, showed the way in hand, had the rail through the bend, was roused the final furlong and kept LAYTON THE DAY at bay. LAYTON THE DAY pressed FEVER NATION from just outside and lacked the extra needed deep stretch. BUREAU well placed inside from the early going, ran evenly in the lane and found himself boxed in through the waning yards. EL RAYO in contention early, did not stay close while saving ground through the bend, angled out widest upper stretch and had no late bid. A MERRY HEART somewhat fractious in the gate, was a factor on the backstretch but began to fade three wide on the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Bureau
ENTRY.OWNER: Pohl Dennis and Gavilsky II Lawrence J
ENTRY.COMMENT: well placed inside, evenly stretch, boxed in late

ENTRY.NAME: El Rayo
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside turn, angled outside stretch, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Layton the Day
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 2 wide, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: A Merry Heart
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious gate, faded 3 wide turn

ENTRY.NAME: Fever Nation
ENTRY.COMMENT: quickly clear, rated inside, urged last 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILDWOOD MINISTRY moved clear of the rest from inside after travelling the first eighth, was just off the rail on the bend, floated out entering the lane, steadily drifted out, held a straight path the final sixteenth and drew off. GRANDDADDYLONGLEGS prominent between horses, went for the lead outside WILDWOOD MINISTRY on the turn, lost ground staying outside the latter into the stretch, altered inside WILDWOOD MINISTRY when that one took his path inside the last eighth, was no match for the leader in the late going but pulled away for the place. SECRET HONOR soon overcame an awkward start to be a contender from outside, closed the gap widest on the bend, lost further ground staying outside GRANDDADDYLONGLEGS into the lane, gradually angled in as he wore down inside the final furlong and narrowly held his position. DRAGGING MAIN void of early speed, was just off the inside taking the turn and had no late bid. MY KINDA TETON was an early factor, saved ground through the bend then gave way for the drive. RA'DOM showed little. The rider of GRANDDADDYLONGLEGS lodged an objection alleging interference from WILDWOOD MINISTRY inside the final furlong. After their review, the stewards did not uphold that claim of foul.

ENTRY.NAME: Ra'dom
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Wildwood Ministry
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, drifted out stretch, clearly best

ENTRY.NAME: My Kinda Teton
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Secret Honor
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward start, 4-path turn, angled in last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Dragging Main
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-path turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Granddaddylonglegs
ENTRY.COMMENT: bid between turn, carried out into stretch, altered in inside 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 67. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGHLY PERFECT in hand early from outside, was let out after two furlongs, came into contention two wide on the bend, quickly took the lead three wide upper stretch, gradually angled in and steadily pulled away under mild urging. ST. LOUIE LOUIE was away somewhat slowly, rushed up from inside to dispute the pace, floated out a bit into the lane, lugged in slightly nearing the eighth pole, angled out inside the final furlong and could only draw clear for second. TRUIST also settled early, commenced his bid after a quarter mile, had the rail through the bend, was steadied as his path narrowed midstretch, altered out and was unchallenged for the show. BLEEDING BLUE slow and somewhat awkward at the break, was hustled up to dispute the pace outside ST. LOUIE LOUIE, began to drift out leaving the turn, continued to drift entering the stretch and steadily gave way. There was a stewards' inquiry into TRUIST'S loss of action midstretch but no action was taken by them after their review.

ENTRY.NAME: St. Louie Louie
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, rushed up inside, 2-path into stretch, best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Bleeding Blue
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, 2 wide speed, drifted out leaving turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Truist
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled early, inside turn, steadied, altered out 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Highly Perfect
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled outside, 2-3 wide turn, mild urging stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REBA ATTACK stalked the early speed from between rivals, went for the lead three wide on the bend, floated out some entering the lane, took the advantage and began to draw off approaching the final sixteenth. TU ROYAL vied for the lead briefly, did not stay with CAHOKIA POSSE after a furlong, came to the latter from just outside on the turn, battled for second in the stretch and began to edge ahead of CAHOKIA POSSE the last sixteenth. CAHOKIA POSSE hesitated at the break, was encouraged to vie for the early lead, moved clear after a furlong, was challenged from outside on the bend, fought for second in the lane but gradually yielded the final sixteenth. NAPABIT crowded briefly at the break, raced in contention from outside on the backstretch, advanced four wide on the turn to threaten, fanned outside REBA ATTACK for the stretch run and could only just hold her position late. TOUR DE' PORT bobbled a bit just after the start, was well placed just off the inside, retreated some on the bend, came into the stretch from path three and also failed to have a stretch bid. LADY WHITE SOX brushed with NAPABIT at the start, was a factor between horses on the backstretch but began to fade nearing the end of three furlongs. CALVIN'S GIRL also somewhat slow at the break, was soon well back, angled in midway on the backstretch, two wide through the turn and had little for the drive. SKIP TO BALI hesitant and somewhat awkward at the start, was an early factor between rivals, moved to the inside nearing the bend and gave way before finishing three furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: Tour De' Port
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path turn, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Cahokia Posse
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start, rushed to lead, inside turn, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Tu Royal
ENTRY.COMMENT: bid 2 wide turn, no match for winner

ENTRY.NAME: Calvin's Girl
ENTRY.OWNER: The Estate of Kenneth H Hutchens
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start, showed little

ENTRY.NAME: Reba Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked between, 3-4 path turn, driven clear

ENTRY.NAME: Skip to Bali
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start, gave way inside early

ENTRY.NAME: Lady White Sox
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded 3 wide turn

ENTRY.NAME: Napabit
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-5 wide turn, leveled off stretch
